  <metadata>
    <name>Areuse gorges</name>
    <desc>This captivating route follows the course of the river Areuse – tranquil one moment, tempestuous the next. Stone bridges, catwalks, stairways, narrow passages through the cliffs and awesome rock walls punctuate this revitalising hike through the gorges.</desc>
    <time>2026-04-28T18:39:27+02:00</time>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/49/374376/1/passerelle-expo02-gorges-areuse-2_800.JPG">
        <text>Steg der Expo.02 in der Areuse-Schlucht (Tourisme neuchâtelois)</text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/349301/1/les-gorges-de-l-areuse_800.jpg">
        <text>Die Areuse-Schlucht </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64215/1/gperret-vdt-gorgesareuse-3_800.jpg">
        <text>Areuse-Schlucht (Guillaume Perret)</text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64217/1/tn-vdt-gorgesareuse-2_800.jpg">
        <text>Areuse-Schlucht </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/64218/1/vbourrut-vdt-gorgesareuse-1_800.jpg">
        <text>Areuse-Schlucht (Vincent Bourrut)</text>
    </link>
      </metadata>

    <wpt lat="46.957381698393" lon="6.7684726166622">
        <ele>618.67596435547</ele>
      
    <name>Nature center &quot;La Morille&quot;</name>
    <desc>Learn all about trout, bats and the region&#039;s caves as you tour this informative exhibition in a pretty half-timbered house. An attraction that&#039;s especially popular with walkers and families.</desc>
    
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/97867/1/morille_800.jpg">
        <text>La Morille </text>
    </link>
      </wpt>
    <wpt lat="46.95755" lon="6.770239">
        <ele>620.37664794922</ele>
      
    <name>Restaurant de La Truite</name>
    <desc>Family restaurant located in the Gorges de l&#039;Areuse, famous for the trout in the fishpond.</desc>
    
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/307944/1/561d7d19d83765ccb117a17ca2decf0898bab7b0_800.jpg">
        <text> </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/307945/1/ed0b157b1ae24f1d3f3823688c537410edd43272_800.jpg">
        <text> </text>
    </link>
      </wpt>
    <wpt lat="46.949456501715" lon="6.8342093104508">
        <ele>477.94827270508</ele>
      
    <name>Museum of vine and wine</name>
    <desc>Learn all about the evolution of winemaking and viticulture within the walls of a majestic castle - also home to the Canton&#039;s wine centre where you can sample Neuchâtel&#039;s finest vintages.</desc>
    
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/67048/2/musee-de-la-vigne-et-du-vin_800.jpg">
        <text>Reben- und Weinmuseum (Tourisme neuchâtelois)</text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/876867/1/museeetage2_800.jpg">
        <text>Weinbau- und Weinmuseum </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/876866/1/museeetage3_800.jpg">
        <text>Weinbau- und Weinmuseum </text>
    </link>
        <link href="https://static.mycity.travel/manage/uploads/8/58/876868/1/museeetage1_800.jpg">
        <text>Weinbau- und Weinmuseum </text>
    </link>
      </wpt>
  
